{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"As a researcher, every once in a while"},{"time":3000,"text":"you encounter something"},{"time":5000,"text":"a little disconcerting."},{"time":7000,"text":"And this is something that changes your understanding of the world around you,"},{"time":10000,"text":"and teaches you that you're very wrong"},{"time":12000,"text":"about something that you really believed firmly in."},{"time":16000,"text":"And these are unfortunate moments,"},{"time":19000,"text":"because you go to sleep that night"},{"time":21000,"text":"dumber than when you woke up."},{"time":24000,"text":"So, that's really the goal of my talk,"},{"time":26000,"text":"is to A, communicate that moment to you"},{"time":28000,"text":"and B, have you leave this session"},{"time":30000,"text":"a little dumber than when you entered."},{"time":32000,"text":"So, I hope I can really accomplish that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35000,"text":"So, this incident that I'm going to describe"},{"time":38000,"text":"really began with some diarrhea."},{"time":41000,"text":"Now, we've known for a long time the cause of diarrhea."},{"time":44000,"text":"That's why there's a glass of water up there."},{"time":47000,"text":"For us, it's a problem, the people in this room."},{"time":49000,"text":"For babies, it's deadly."},{"time":52000,"text":"They lack nutrients, and diarrhea dehydrates them."},{"time":56000,"text":"And so, as a result, there is a lot of death,"},{"time":58000,"text":"a lot of death."},{"time":61000,"text":"In India in 1960,"},{"time":63000,"text":"there was a 24 percent child mortality rate,"},{"time":65000,"text":"lots of people didn't make it. This is incredibly unfortunate."},{"time":69000,"text":"One of the big reasons this happened was"},{"time":71000,"text":"because of diarrhea."},{"time":73000,"text":"Now, there was a big effort to solve this problem,"},{"time":76000,"text":"and there was actually a big solution."},{"time":80000,"text":"This solution has been called, by some,"},{"time":82000,"text":"\"potentially the most important medical"},{"time":84000,"text":"advance this century.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":87000,"text":"Now, the solution turned out to be simple."},{"time":90000,"text":"And what it was was oral rehydration salts."},{"time":94000,"text":"Many of you have probably used this."},{"time":96000,"text":"It's brilliant. It's a way to get sodium"},{"time":98000,"text":"and glucose together so that when you add it to water"},{"time":101000,"text":"the child is able to absorb it even during situations of diarrhea."},{"time":104000,"text":"Remarkable impact on mortality."},{"time":108000,"text":"Massive solution to the problem."},{"time":110000,"text":"Flash forward: 1960, 24 percent child mortality"},{"time":113000,"text":"has dropped to 6.5 percent today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115000,"text":"Still a big number, but a big drop."},{"time":118000,"text":"It looks like the technological problem is solved."},{"time":121000,"text":"But if you look, even today"},{"time":123000,"text":"there are about 400,000 diarrhea-related deaths"},{"time":125000,"text":"in India alone."},{"time":127000,"text":"What's going on here?"},{"time":129000,"text":"Well the easy answer is, we just haven't gotten those salts"},{"time":132000,"text":"to those people."},{"time":134000,"text":"That's actually not true."},{"time":136000,"text":"If you look in areas where these salts are completely available,"},{"time":139000,"text":"the price is low or zero, these deaths still continue abated."},{"time":142000,"text":"Maybe there's a biological answer."},{"time":144000,"text":"Maybe these are the deaths that simple rehydration"},{"time":146000,"text":"alone doesn't solve. That's not true either."},{"time":149000,"text":"Many of these deaths were completely preventable,"},{"time":154000,"text":"and this what I want to think of as the disconcerting thing,"},{"time":157000,"text":"what I want to call \"the last mile\" problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159000,"text":"See, we spent a lot of energy, in many domains --"},{"time":163000,"text":"technological, scientific, hard work,"},{"time":165000,"text":"creativity, human ingenuity --"},{"time":167000,"text":"to crack important social problems with technology solutions."},{"time":171000,"text":"That's been the discoveries of the last 2,000 years,"},{"time":173000,"text":"that's mankind moving forward."},{"time":175000,"text":"But in this case we cracked it,"},{"time":178000,"text":"but a big part of the problem still remains."},{"time":180000,"text":"Nine hundred and ninety-nine miles went well,"},{"time":182000,"text":"the last mile's proving incredibly stubborn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":185000,"text":"Now, that's for oral rehydration therapy."},{"time":189000,"text":"Maybe this is something unique about diarrhea."},{"time":191000,"text":"Well, it turns out -- and this is where things get really disconcerting --"},{"time":193000,"text":"it's not unique to diarrhea."},{"time":195000,"text":"It's not even unique to poor people in India."},{"time":197000,"text":"Here's an example from a variety of contexts."},{"time":200000,"text":"I've put a bunch of examples up here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":202000,"text":"I'll start with insulin, diabetes"},{"time":205000,"text":"medication in the U.S."},{"time":207000,"text":"OK, the American population."},{"time":209000,"text":"On Medicaid -- if you're fairly poor you get Medicaid,"},{"time":211000,"text":"or if you have health insurance -- insulin is pretty straightforward."},{"time":213000,"text":"You get it, either in pill form or you get it as an injection;"},{"time":217000,"text":"you have to take it every day to maintain your blood sugar levels."},{"time":219000,"text":"Massive technological advance:"},{"time":221000,"text":"took an incredibly deadly disease, made it solvable."},{"time":223000,"text":"Adherence rates. How many people are taking their insulin every day?"},{"time":226000,"text":"About on average, a typical person is taking it 75 percent of the time."},{"time":230000,"text":"As a result, 25,000 people a year go blind,"},{"time":235000,"text":"hundreds of thousands lose limbs, every year,"},{"time":237000,"text":"for something that's solvable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":239000,"text":"Here I have a bunch of other examples,"},{"time":241000,"text":"all suffer from the last mile problem."},{"time":243000,"text":"It's not just medicine."},{"time":245000,"text":"Here's another example from technology:"},{"time":247000,"text":"agriculture. We think"},{"time":249000,"text":"there's a food problem, so we create new seeds."},{"time":251000,"text":"We think there's an income problem, so we create"},{"time":253000,"text":"new ways of farming that increase income."},{"time":256000,"text":"Well, look at some old ways, some ways that we'd already cracked."},{"time":259000,"text":"Intercropping. Intercropping really increases income."},{"time":261000,"text":"Sometimes in rice we found incredible increases in yield"},{"time":264000,"text":"when you mix different varieties of rice side by side."},{"time":266000,"text":"Some people are doing that,"},{"time":268000,"text":"many are not. What's going on?"},{"time":270000,"text":"This is the last mile."},{"time":272000,"text":"The last mile is, everywhere, problematic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274000,"text":"Alright, what's the problem?"},{"time":276000,"text":"The problem is this little three-pound machine"},{"time":279000,"text":"that's behind your eyes and between your ears."},{"time":283000,"text":"This machine is really strange,"},{"time":285000,"text":"and one of the consequences is that people are weird."},{"time":289000,"text":"They do lots of inconsistent things."},{"time":293000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":295000,"text":"They do lots of inconsistent things."},{"time":298000,"text":"And the inconsistencies"},{"time":300000,"text":"create, fundamentally, this last mile problem."},{"time":303000,"text":"See, when we were dealing with our biology, bacteria,"},{"time":306000,"text":"the genes, the things inside here, the blood?"},{"time":309000,"text":"That's complex, but it's manageable."},{"time":312000,"text":"When we're dealing with people like this?"},{"time":315000,"text":"The mind is more complex."},{"time":317000,"text":"That's not as manageable, and that's what we're struggling with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319000,"text":"Let me go back to diarrhea for a second."},{"time":322000,"text":"Here's a question that was asked in the National Sample Survey,"},{"time":325000,"text":"which is a survey asked of many Indian women:"},{"time":327000,"text":"\"Your child has diarrhea."},{"time":329000,"text":"Should you increase, maintain or decrease the number of fluids?\""},{"time":332000,"text":"Just so you don't embarrass yourselves, I'll give you the right answer:"},{"time":335000,"text":"It's increase."},{"time":339000,"text":"Now, diarrhea's interesting"},{"time":340000,"text":"because it's been around for thousands of years,"},{"time":342000,"text":"ever since humankind really"},{"time":345000,"text":"lived side by side enough to have really polluted water."},{"time":348000,"text":"One Roman strategy that was very interesting"},{"time":350000,"text":"was that -- and it really gave them a comparative advantage --"},{"time":352000,"text":"they made sure their soldiers didn't drink"},{"time":355000,"text":"even remotely muddied waters."},{"time":357000,"text":"Because if some of your troops get diarrhea they're not that effective"},{"time":360000,"text":"on the battlefield."},{"time":362000,"text":"So, if you think of Roman comparative advantage part of it was the breast shields,"},{"time":364000,"text":"the breastplates, but part of it was drinking the right water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":368000,"text":"So, here are these women. They've seen their parents"},{"time":370000,"text":"have struggled with diarrhea, they've struggled with diarrhea,"},{"time":372000,"text":"they've seen lots of deaths. How do they answer this question?"},{"time":375000,"text":"In India, 35 to 50 percent say \"Reduce.\""},{"time":379000,"text":"Think about what that means for a second."},{"time":381000,"text":"Thirty-five to 50 percent of women"},{"time":383000,"text":"forget oral rehydration therapy,"},{"time":385000,"text":"they are increasing --"},{"time":387000,"text":"they are actually making their child"},{"time":390000,"text":"more likely to die through their actions."},{"time":393000,"text":"How is that possible?"},{"time":395000,"text":"Well, one possibility -- I think that's how most people respond to this --"},{"time":398000,"text":"is to say, \"That's just stupid.\""},{"time":402000,"text":"I don't think that's stupid."},{"time":404000,"text":"I think there is something very profoundly right in what these women are doing."},{"time":407000,"text":"And that is, you don't put water"},{"time":409000,"text":"into a leaky bucket."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411000,"text":"So, think of the mental model that goes behind reducing the intake."},{"time":415000,"text":"Just doesn't make sense."},{"time":417000,"text":"Now, the model is intuitively right."},{"time":420000,"text":"It just doesn't happen to be right about the world."},{"time":424000,"text":"But it makes a whole lot of sense at some deep level."},{"time":427000,"text":"And that, to me, is the fundamental challenge"},{"time":430000,"text":"of the last mile."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435000,"text":"This first challenge is what I refer to as the persuasion challenge."},{"time":438000,"text":"Convincing people to do something --"},{"time":440000,"text":"take oral rehydration therapy, intercrop, whatever it might be --"},{"time":442000,"text":"is not an act of information:"},{"time":445000,"text":"\"Let's give them the data,"},{"time":447000,"text":"and when they have data they'll do the right thing.\""},{"time":449000,"text":"It's more complex than that."},{"time":451000,"text":"And if you want to understand how it's more complex"},{"time":453000,"text":"let me start with something kind of interesting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":457000,"text":"I'm going to give you a little math problem,"},{"time":459000,"text":"and I want you to just yell out the answer as fast as possible."},{"time":462000,"text":"A bat and a ball together cost $1.10."},{"time":464000,"text":"The bat costs a dollar more than the ball."},{"time":467000,"text":"How much does the ball cost? Quick."},{"time":470000,"text":"So, somebody out there says, \"Five.\""},{"time":472000,"text":"A lot of you said, \"Ten.\""},{"time":474000,"text":"Let's think about 10 for a second."},{"time":477000,"text":"If the ball costs 10, the bat costs..."},{"time":481000,"text":"this is easy, $1.10."},{"time":483000,"text":"Yeah. So, together they would cost $1.20."},{"time":486000,"text":"So, here you all are, ostensibly educated people."},{"time":489000,"text":"Most of you look smart."},{"time":492000,"text":"The combination of that produces"},{"time":495000,"text":"something that is actually, you got this thing wrong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":497000,"text":"How is that possible? Let's go to something else."},{"time":500000,"text":"I know algebra can be complicated."},{"time":503000,"text":"So, let's dial this back. That's what? Fifth grade? Fourth grade?"},{"time":506000,"text":"Let's go back to kindergarten. OK?"},{"time":509000,"text":"There's a great show on American television that you have to watch."},{"time":511000,"text":"It's called \"Are You Smarter Than a Fifth Grader?\""},{"time":513000,"text":"I think we've learned the answer to that here."},{"time":516000,"text":"Let's move to kindergarten. Let's see if we can beat five-year-olds."},{"time":519000,"text":"Here's what I'm going to do: I'm going to put objects on the screen."},{"time":522000,"text":"I just want you to name the color of the object."},{"time":526000,"text":"That's all it is. OK?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":528000,"text":"I want you to do it fast, and say it out loud with me,"},{"time":531000,"text":"and do it quickly. I'll make the first one easy for you."},{"time":533000,"text":"Ready? Black."},{"time":535000,"text":"Now the next ones I want you to do quickly and say it out loud."},{"time":537000,"text":"Ready? Go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539000,"text":"Audience: Red. Green."},{"time":541000,"text":"Yellow. Blue. Red."},{"time":543000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":546000,"text":"Sendhil Mullainathan: That's pretty good."},{"time":550000,"text":"Almost out of kindergarten."},{"time":552000,"text":"What is all this telling us?"},{"time":554000,"text":"You see, what's going on here, and in the bat and ball problem"},{"time":557000,"text":"is that you have some intuitive ways of interacting with the world,"},{"time":560000,"text":"some models that you use to understand the world."},{"time":562000,"text":"These models, like the leaky bucket,"},{"time":564000,"text":"work well in most situations."},{"time":566000,"text":"I suspect most of you --"},{"time":568000,"text":"I hope that's true for the rest of you --"},{"time":570000,"text":"actually do pretty well with addition and subtraction in the real world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":574000,"text":"I found a problem, a specific problem"},{"time":576000,"text":"that actually found an error with that."},{"time":579000,"text":"Diarrhea, and many last mile problems, are like that."},{"time":581000,"text":"They are situations where the mental model"},{"time":583000,"text":"doesn't match the reality."},{"time":585000,"text":"Same thing here:"},{"time":587000,"text":"You had an intuitive response to this that was very quick."},{"time":589000,"text":"You read \"blue\" and you wanted to say \"blue,\" even though you knew your task was red."}]},{"cues":[{"time":592000,"text":"Now, I do this stuff because it's fun."},{"time":594000,"text":"But it's more profound than fun."},{"time":598000,"text":"I'll give you a good example of how it actually effects persuasion."},{"time":601000,"text":"BMW is a pretty safe car."},{"time":604000,"text":"And they are trying to figure out, \"Safety is good."},{"time":606000,"text":"I want to advertise safety. How am I going to advertise safety?\""},{"time":608000,"text":"\"I could give people numbers. We do well on crash tests.\""},{"time":611000,"text":"But the truth of the matter is, you look at that car,"},{"time":613000,"text":"it doesn't look like a Volvo,"},{"time":615000,"text":"and it doesn't look like a Hummer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":617000,"text":"So, what I want you to think about for a few minutes"},{"time":619000,"text":"is: How would you convey safety of the BMW? Okay?"},{"time":622000,"text":"So now, while you're thinking about that let's move to a second task."},{"time":625000,"text":"The second task is fuel efficiency. Okay?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":628000,"text":"Here's another puzzle for all of you."},{"time":630000,"text":"One person walks into a car lot,"},{"time":632000,"text":"and they're thinking about buying this Toyota Yaris."},{"time":635000,"text":"They are saying, \"This is 35 miles per gallon. I'm going to do"},{"time":637000,"text":"the environmentally right thing, I'm going to buy the Prius,"},{"time":639000,"text":"50 miles per gallon.\""},{"time":641000,"text":"Another person walks into the lot,"},{"time":643000,"text":"and they're about to buy a Hummer, nine miles per gallon,"},{"time":645000,"text":"fully loaded, luxury."},{"time":647000,"text":"And they say, \"You know what? Do I need turbo? Do I need this heavyweight car?\""},{"time":651000,"text":"I'm going to do something good for the environment."},{"time":653000,"text":"I'm going to take off some of that weight,"},{"time":655000,"text":"and I'm going to buy a Hummer that's 11 miles per gallon.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":658000,"text":"Which one of these people has done more for the environment?"},{"time":661000,"text":"See, you have a mental model."},{"time":663000,"text":"Fifty versus 35, that's a big move. Eleven versus nine? Come on."},{"time":666000,"text":"Turns out, go home and do the math,"},{"time":669000,"text":"the nine to 11 is a bigger change. That person has saved more gallons."},{"time":672000,"text":"Why? Because we don't care about miles per gallon, we care about"},{"time":674000,"text":"gallons per mile."},{"time":676000,"text":"Think about how powerful that is if you're trying to encourage fuel efficiency."},{"time":679000,"text":"Miles per gallon is the way we present things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":681000,"text":"If we want to encourage change of behavior,"},{"time":684000,"text":"gallons per mile would have far more effectiveness."},{"time":686000,"text":"Researchers have found these type of anomalies."},{"time":689000,"text":"Okay, back to BMW. What should they do?"},{"time":692000,"text":"The problem BMW faces is this car looks safe."},{"time":695000,"text":"This car, which is my Mini, doesn't look that safe."},{"time":699000,"text":"Here was BMW's brilliant insight, which they embodied into an ad campaign."},{"time":702000,"text":"They showed a BMW driving down the street."},{"time":704000,"text":"There's a truck on the right. Boxes fall out of the truck."},{"time":707000,"text":"The car swerves to avoid it, and therefore doesn't get into an accident."}]},{"cues":[{"time":712000,"text":"BWM realizes safety, in people's minds, has two components."},{"time":716000,"text":"You can be safe because when you're hit, you survive,"},{"time":720000,"text":"or you can be safe because you avoid accidents."},{"time":722000,"text":"Remarkably successful campaign, but notice the power of it."},{"time":724000,"text":"It harnesses something you already believe."},{"time":727000,"text":"Now, even if I persuaded you to do something,"},{"time":731000,"text":"it's hard sometimes to actually get action as a result."},{"time":735000,"text":"You all probably intended to wake up,"},{"time":737000,"text":"I don't know, 6:30, 7 a.m."},{"time":740000,"text":"This is a battle we all fight every day,"},{"time":742000,"text":"along with trying to get to the gym."},{"time":745000,"text":"Now, this is an example of that battle,"},{"time":748000,"text":"and makes us realize intentions don't always translate into action,"},{"time":751000,"text":"and so one of the fundamental challenges"},{"time":753000,"text":"is how we would actually do that. OK?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":757000,"text":"So, let me now talk about the last mile problem."},{"time":760000,"text":"So far, I've been pretty negative."},{"time":763000,"text":"I've been trying to show you the oddities of human behavior."},{"time":766000,"text":"And I think maybe I'm being too negative."},{"time":768000,"text":"Maybe it's the diarrhea."},{"time":770000,"text":"Maybe the last mile problem really should be thought of"},{"time":772000,"text":"as the last mile opportunity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":774000,"text":"Let's go back to diabetes."},{"time":776000,"text":"This is a typical insulin injection."},{"time":779000,"text":"Now, carrying this thing around is complicated."},{"time":782000,"text":"You gotta carry the bottle, you gotta carry the syringe."},{"time":786000,"text":"It's also painful."},{"time":788000,"text":"Now, you may think to yourself, \"Well, if my eyes depended on it,"},{"time":792000,"text":"you know, I would obviously use it every day.\""},{"time":794000,"text":"But the pain, the discomfort,"},{"time":796000,"text":"you know, paying attention, remembering to put it in your purse"},{"time":798000,"text":"when you go on a long trip:"},{"time":800000,"text":"These are the day-to-day of life, and they do pose problems."},{"time":804000,"text":"Here is an innovation, a design innovation."},{"time":807000,"text":"This is a pen, it's called an insulin pen, preloaded."},{"time":811000,"text":"The needle is particularly sharp."},{"time":812000,"text":"You just gotta carry this thing around."},{"time":814000,"text":"It's much easier to use, much less painful."},{"time":816000,"text":"Anywhere between five and 10 percent increase in adherence,"},{"time":820000,"text":"just as a result of this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":822000,"text":"That's what I'm talking about as a last mile opportunity."},{"time":825000,"text":"You see, we tend to think the problem is solved"},{"time":828000,"text":"when we solve the technology problem."},{"time":830000,"text":"But the human innovation, the human problem"},{"time":832000,"text":"still remains, and that's a great frontier that we have left."},{"time":836000,"text":"This isn't about the biology of people;"},{"time":838000,"text":"this is now about the brains, the psychology of people,"},{"time":842000,"text":"and innovation needs to continue all the way through"},{"time":844000,"text":"the last mile."}]},{"cues":[{"time":846000,"text":"Here's another example of this."},{"time":848000,"text":"This is from a company called Positive Energy."},{"time":851000,"text":"This is about energy efficiency."},{"time":853000,"text":"We're spending a lot of time on fuel cells right now."},{"time":856000,"text":"What this company does is they send a letter"},{"time":858000,"text":"to households that say, \"Here's your energy use,"},{"time":860000,"text":"here's your neighbor's energy use: You're doing well.\" Smiley face."},{"time":863000,"text":"\"You're doing worse.\" Frown."},{"time":865000,"text":"And what they find is just this letter, nothing else,"},{"time":868000,"text":"has a two to three percent reduction in electricity use."}]},{"cues":[{"time":870000,"text":"And you want to think about the social value of that"},{"time":872000,"text":"in terms of carbon offsets, reduced electricity,"},{"time":874000,"text":"900 million dollars per year."},{"time":876000,"text":"Why? Because for free,"},{"time":878000,"text":"this isn't a new technology, this is a letter --"},{"time":880000,"text":"we're getting a Big Bang in behavior."},{"time":882000,"text":"So, how do we tackle the last mile?"},{"time":886000,"text":"I think this tells us there is an opportunity."},{"time":889000,"text":"And I think to tackle it, we need to combine"},{"time":891000,"text":"psychology,"},{"time":893000,"text":"marketing,"},{"time":895000,"text":"art, we've seen that."},{"time":897000,"text":"But you know what we need to combine it with?"},{"time":899000,"text":"We need to combine this with the scientific method."}]},{"cues":[{"time":901000,"text":"See what's really puzzling and frustrating about the last mile, to me,"},{"time":905000,"text":"is that the first 999 miles are all about science."},{"time":908000,"text":"No one would say, \"Hey, I think this medicine works, go ahead and use it.\""},{"time":912000,"text":"We have testing, we go to the lab, we try it again, we have refinement."},{"time":914000,"text":"But you know what we do on the last mile?"},{"time":917000,"text":"\"Oh, this is a good idea. People will like this. Let's put it out there.\""},{"time":920000,"text":"The amount of resources we put in are disparate."},{"time":922000,"text":"We put billions of dollars into fuel-efficient technologies."},{"time":925000,"text":"How much are we putting into"},{"time":927000,"text":"energy behavior change"},{"time":929000,"text":"in a credible, systematic, testing way?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":932000,"text":"Now, I think that we're on the verge of something big."},{"time":935000,"text":"We're on the verge of a whole new social science."},{"time":938000,"text":"It's a social science that recognizes --"},{"time":940000,"text":"much like science recognizes the complexity of the body,"},{"time":943000,"text":"biology recognizes the complexity of the body -- we'll recognize"},{"time":945000,"text":"the complexity of the human mind."},{"time":947000,"text":"The careful testing, retesting, design,"},{"time":949000,"text":"are going to open up vistas of understanding,"},{"time":952000,"text":"complexities, difficult things."},{"time":954000,"text":"And those vistas will both create new science,"},{"time":957000,"text":"and fundamental change in the world as we see it, in the next hundred years."},{"time":961000,"text":"All right. Thank you very much."},{"time":963000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":965000,"text":"Chris Anderson: Sendhil, thank you so much."},{"time":967000,"text":"So, this whole area is so fascinating."},{"time":970000,"text":"I mean, it sometimes feels, listening to behavioral economists"},{"time":973000,"text":"that they are kind of putting into place"},{"time":976000,"text":"academically, what great marketers"},{"time":978000,"text":"have sort of intuitively known for a long time."},{"time":981000,"text":"How much is your field talking to great marketers"},{"time":985000,"text":"about their insights into human psychology?"},{"time":987000,"text":"Because they've seen it on the ground."}]},{"cues":[{"time":989000,"text":"Sendhil Mullainathan: Yeah, we spend a lot of time talking to marketers,"},{"time":991000,"text":"and I think 60 percent of it is exactly what you say,"},{"time":994000,"text":"there are insights to be gleaned there."},{"time":996000,"text":"Forty percent of it is about what marketing is."},{"time":998000,"text":"Marketing is selling an ad to a firm."},{"time":1003000,"text":"So, in some sense, a lot of marketing is about"},{"time":1005000,"text":"convincing a CEO, \"This is a good ad campaign.\""},{"time":1008000,"text":"So, there is a little bit of slippage there."},{"time":1010000,"text":"That's just a caveat. That's different from actually having an effective ad campaign."},{"time":1014000,"text":"And one of the new movements in marketing is: How do we actually"},{"time":1016000,"text":"measure effectiveness? Are we effective?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1018000,"text":"CA: How you take your insights here"},{"time":1022000,"text":"and actually get them integrated"},{"time":1025000,"text":"into working business models on the ground,"},{"time":1028000,"text":"in Indian villages, for example?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1030000,"text":"SM: So, the scientific method I alluded to is pretty important."},{"time":1033000,"text":"We work closely with companies that have operational capacity,"},{"time":1035000,"text":"or nonprofits that have operational capacity."},{"time":1037000,"text":"And then we say, \"Well, you want to get this behavior change."},{"time":1039000,"text":"Let's come up with a few ideas, test them,"},{"time":1042000,"text":"see which is working, go back, synthesize,"},{"time":1044000,"text":"and try to come up with a thing that works,\""},{"time":1046000,"text":"and then we're able to scale with partners."},{"time":1048000,"text":"It's kind of the model that has worked in other contexts."},{"time":1050000,"text":"If you have biological problems"},{"time":1052000,"text":"we try and fix it, see if it works, and then work the scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1054000,"text":"CA: Alright Sendhil, thanks so much for coming to TED. Thank you."},{"time":1057000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}